ABUJA – Over 20 people are trapped after a four-story hotel building collapsed in Dape, Life Camp, Abuja. Our correspondent gathered that the hotel was owned by Summit Villa hotel services. Eyewitnesses on the scene report that more than 20 people are stuck in the hotel’s underground. As at the time of filling this report, the FCT Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) and Department of Development Control are on the ground to rescue the trapped victims.